  "description": [
    "GAS SUPPLY NO WORRY FOR BUYERS OF AUTOS Scientific Opinion Contradicts Rumors of Growing Shortage But Conservation of Vast Store Is Counseled THOSJS who conclude that the only thing to do is buy a new automobile after visiting the annual automobile show prob ably will not give a thought to the often heard rumor that gasoline supplies are getting low It is wise that they do not for the best scientific opinion is decidedly contrary to the rumor Gasoline supplies will be sufficient to meet the needs of the vastly in creasing motoring public for many years says D H Killeffer secretary of the New York Section American hemical Society At t lie same time lie points out that there is a clear need for conservation of the available motor fuels On the subject of fuel resources he says Most statements on the subject of petroleum reserves are little more than opinions Geologists have been able so determine with some degree of accu racy the area of oil deposits by drill lug wells but even the most careful estimates of the amount of oil to be Obtained from any deposit are subject to unavoidable errors which make make them merely"
